{'chapter_title': 'Bhagavad Gita: Chapter 18, Verse 10', 'sanskrit': ['न द्वेष्ट्यकुशलं कर्म कुशले नानुषज्जते |', 'त्यागी सत्त्वसमाविष्टो मेधावी छिन्नसंशय: || 10||'], 'latin': ['na dveṣhṭy akuśhalaṁ karma kuśhale nānuṣhajjate', 'tyāgī sattva-samāviṣhṭo medhāvī chhinna-sanśhayaḥ'], 'translation': ['\r\n                            ', '\r\n                            Those who neither avoid disagreeable work nor seek work because it is agreeable are persons of true renunciation. They are endowed with the quality of the mode of goodness and have no doubts (about the nature of work).\r\n                        ']}